# ============================================================
# IMPORTANT: What TO COMMIT
# ============================================================
# ✅ Source code: src/main/scala/**/*.scala
# ✅ Test code: src/test/scala/**/*.scala
# ✅ Proto files: src/main/protobuf/**/*.proto
# ✅ Build config: build.sbt, project/build.properties, project/plugins.sbt
# ✅ Documentation: docs/**/*.md, plan/**/*.md, README.md
# ✅ This file: .gitignore

# ============================================================
# IMPORTANT: What NOT TO COMMIT
# ============================================================
# ❌ Binary files: *.class, *.jar
# ❌ IDE files: .idea/, *.iml
# ❌ Build outputs: target/
# ❌ Test artifacts: test-output/, *.dat
# ❌ Logs: *.log
# ❌ Temporary files: *.tmp, .cache

# ============================================================
# Verification Command
# ============================================================
# Before committing, always run:
#   1. sbt clean
#   2. git status (check for unwanted files)
#   3. git add <specific-files>  (NOT "git add -A"!)
#   4. git commit -m "message"
#
# To check what will be committed:
#   git diff --staged
# ============================================================
